==English==

===Etymology===

From German ''Zirkon'', < Arabic ''zarqun'', < Persian ''zargon'', "gold-colored" (''zar'' meaning "gold").

===Noun===
'''zircon'''

#A mineral occurring in [[tetragonal]] crystals, usually of a brown or grey/gray colour/color. It consists of [[silica]] and [[zirconia]].

